Visualize network using ggraph. There are many choices of layouts, or, ways to organize the position of nodes and edges. Choice of layout will depend on structure of the network. Play with some options to see what works.

Centrality measures are one of the first steps in network analysis. They are descriptive statistics. Degree centrality counts number of edges going into or out of each node. Closeness centrality measures the average shortest path from one node to each other node. Betweenness centrality measures the number of times a node acts as a bridge between two other nodes (along the shortest path).

Because centrality describes the nodes, access them using the function V() on the graph/network object.

# Compute measures of centrality
# Degree centrality
V(graph)$indegree = degree(graph, mode = 'in')
V(graph)$outdegree = degree(graph, mode = 'out')

# Closeness centrality
V(graph)$closeness = closeness(graph)

# Betweenness centrality
V(graph)$betweenness = betweenness(graph)

Centrality measures are now stored as a new attribute in the vertex (node) list.

# Examine node/vertex and edge attributes

Below, a function to iteratively remove nodes based on centrality measures. Were going to test the resilience of the network

# TAKEN FROM:
#     https://users.dimi.uniud.it/~massimo.franceschet/R/resilience.html
#
percolate = function(g, size, d) {
  
  giant = vector()
  
  # initial size of giant component
  c = components(g)
  giant[1] = max(c$csize)
  
  names(d) = 1:length(d)
  d = sort(d, decreasing=TRUE)
  vital = as.integer(names(d[1:size]))
  
  for (i in 1:size) {
    c = components(delete_vertices(g, vital[1:i]))
    giant[i+1] = max(c$csize)
  }
  
  return(giant)
  
}

How sensitive is the network structure to a few key individuals? Assess network cohesion

# Resilience/cohesion
size = vcount(graph)/2
# random
rand = percolate(graph, size, d = sample(V(graph), size))    
# degree
deg = percolate(graph, size, d = degree(graph))
# betweenness
bet = percolate(graph, size, d = betweenness(graph))    

plot(0:size, deg, type = "l", col=1, xlab="Number of removed nodes", ylab="Size of giant component")
lines(0:size, bet, col=2)
lines(0:size, rand, col=3)
legend(x = "topright", legend = c("deg", "btw", "rand"), lty = 1, col = 1:3)
